parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering pump fails
causing the steering wheel to become hard to turn
the vehicle to pull to one side
or the power steering to fail intermittently. In some cases
the failure is accompanied by a burning smell
smoke
or a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electro-hydraulic power steering pump can cause the power steering system to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The electro-hydraulic power steering pump fails
causing the power steering system to malfunction
resulting in difficult steering
loss of power steering
or intermittent power steering failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the harmonic balancer can cause the power steering system to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The harmonic balancer separates
causing the power steering system to malfunction
resulting in difficult steering
loss of power steering
or intermittent power steering failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Conditioning and Blower Motor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning and blower motor system can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The air conditioning and blower motor system fails
causing no air or heat to come out of the vents
and water to accumulate in the driver-side foot well.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience sudden loss of power
loud noises
RPM jumps
or difficulty accelerating. In some cases
the vehicle may stall or become undrivable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and spontaneous cracking of the windshield can cause a loss of visibility, potentially leading to accidents, and may also compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle.
symptoms: Cracks or fractures in the windshield
often originating from the bottom center or edges of the glass
and spreading upwards or laterally.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power windows can cause inconvenience, discomfort, and potentially lead to emergency situations where the window is the only means of egress.
symptoms: Windows that stutter
stick
or fail to open/close
often accompanied by electrical issues
and may be more frequent during hot weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiper motor can cause reduced visibility during heavy rain or snow, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Wipers that fail to operate or operate intermittently
often accompanied by electrical issues.
